From https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_Flexible_Box_Layout/Basic_Concepts_of_Flexbox

<html>
<head>
<style>
   .box {
            display: flex;
          }
</style>
</head>
<body>


 <div class="box">
          <div>One</div>
          <div>Two</div>
          <div>Three
              <br>has
              <br>extra
              <br>text
          </div>


</body>
</html>

Now with Grid:
From https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/grid-template-rows

<html>
<head>
<style>
#grid {
  display: grid;
  height: 100px;
  grid-template-rows: 30px 1fr;
}

#areaA {
  background-color: lime;
}

#areaB {
  background-color: yellow;
}
 
          }
</style>
</head>
<body>


<div id="grid">
  <div id="areaA">This is a title</div>
  <div id="areaB">This is Another Title</div>
</div>
</body>
</html>

